Project Overview  BioMove NLMR (Neutral Landscape Models in R) Multidimensionality of Stability AFT (Animal Functional Type Approach) #TidyTuesday  BioMove The DFG funded Research Training Group &lsquo;Integrating Biodiversity Research with Movement Ecology in dynamic agricultural landscapes (BioMove)&rsquo; aims to:
 link innovative individual research projects that overcome the apparent gap between movement ecology and biodiversity research, employing a joint conceptual framework;
 strategically combine empirical, experimental and modelling approaches based in one common study area (AgroScapeLab-Quillow, Brandenburg, Germany) of sufficient size to address questions of varying spatial scales;
